ciscoVpcMIB.name: ciscoVpcMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoVpcMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoVpcMIB.description: This MIB module defines MIB objects which provide management information for configuring and monitoring of Virtual Port Channel(VPC) on Cisco devices. The following terms are used throughout this MIB: ISSU: In Service Software Upgrade ToS: Type of Service UDP: User Datagram Protocol VPC: Virtual Port Channel VRF: Virtual Routing and Forwarding

cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigTable.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigTable
cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigTable.description: The table contains the VPC peer-keepalive link and message configuration information in the managed device.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigEntry.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigEntry
cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigEntry.description: An entry containing VPC peer-keepalive link and message configuration information.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigDomainID.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigDomainID
cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigDomainID.description: An arbitrary value to uniquely identify the VPC management domain on the local system. Value zero indicates no VPC management domain has been configured for this device.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveDestAddrType.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveDestAddrType
cVpcPeerKeepAliveDestAddrType.description: This object specifies type of Internet address of destination address for peer device.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveDestAddr.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveDestAddr
cVpcPeerKeepAliveDestAddr.description: This object specifies destination ip address of peer device. The type of this address is determined by the cVpcPeerKeepAliveDestAddrType object.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveSourceAddrType.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveSourceAddrType
cVpcPeerKeepAliveSourceAddrType.description: This object specifies type of Internet address of source address used for peer-keepalive hello messages.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveSourceAddr.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveSourceAddr
cVpcPeerKeepAliveSourceAddr.description: This object specifies source address used in this peer-keepalive hello messages. The type of this address is determined by the cVpcPeerKeepAliveSourceAddrType object.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveUdpPort.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveUdpPort
cVpcPeerKeepAliveUdpPort.description: This object specifies UDP Port number used for peer-keepalive hello messages.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveInterval.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveInterval
cVpcPeerKeepAliveInterval.description: This object specifies the interval of peer-keepalive hello messages.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveTimeout.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveTimeout
cVpcPeerKeepAliveTimeout.description: This object specifies the timeout of peer-keepalive hello messages.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveHoldTimeout.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveHoldTimeout
cVpcPeerKeepAliveHoldTimeout.description: This object specifies hold timeout to ignore stale peer alive messages.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveTos.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveTos
cVpcPeerKeepAliveTos.description: This object specifies the ToS value used for peer-keepalive hello messages.

cVpcPeerKeepAlivePrecedence.name: cVpcPeerKeepAlivePrecedence
cVpcPeerKeepAlivePrecedence.description: This object specifies the Precedence value used for peer-keepalive hello messages.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveTosByte.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveTosByte
cVpcPeerKeepAliveTosByte.description: This object specifies the ToS-Byte value used for peer-keepalive messages. Only low eight-bit byte of this double word is used. Bit 0 is reserved. Bits 1 to 5 represent the value of cVpcPeerKeepAliveTos. Bits 6 to 8 come into cVpcPeerKeepAlivePrecedence. ToS-Byte indicates the value of the whole byte including ToS, Precedence and reserved bit 0.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveVrfName.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveVrfName
cVpcPeerKeepAliveVrfName.description: This object specifies the VRF name to be used for peer-keepalive messages routing.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveTable.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveTable
cVpcPeerKeepAliveTable.description: The table contains the VPC peer-keepalive link status information in the managed device.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveEntry.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveEntry
cVpcPeerKeepAliveEntry.description: An entry containing VPC peer-keepalive link status information.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveDomainID.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveDomainID
cVpcPeerKeepAliveDomainID.description: An arbitrary value to uniquely identify the VPC management domain on the local system. Value zero indicates there is no VPC management domain being configured for this device.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveStatus.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveStatus
cVpcPeerKeepAliveStatus.description: This object indicates VPC peer keep-alive status. disabled(1) : Peer-keepalive is disabled. alive(2) : Peer-keepalive is alive. peerUnreachable(3) : Peer is unreachable through Peer-keepalive link. aliveButDomainIdDismatch(4) : Peer-keepalive is alive, but VPC domain doesn't match with each other. suspendedAsISSU(5) : Peer-keepalive is suspended during ISSU. suspendedAsDestIPUnreachable(6) : Peer-keepalive is suspended since destination ip is unreachable. suspendedAsVRFUnusable(7) : Peer-keepalive is suspended since the current VRF is unusable. misconfigured(8) : Misconfigure Peer-keepalive feature.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveTime.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveTime
cVpcPeerKeepAliveTime.description: This object indicates the time (in msec) since the peer became alive. It will hold value 0 if peer-keepalive never becomes alive.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgSendStatus.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgSendStatus
cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgSendStatus.description: This object indicates VPC peer keep-alive message sending status.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgLastSendTime.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgLastSendTime
cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgLastSendTime.description: This object indicates date and time of VPC peer keep-alive message last send. This object contains value 0x0000010100000000, if peer-keepalive message has never been sent.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgSendInterface.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgSendInterface
cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgSendInterface.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of interface of VPC peer keep-alive message sent on.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgRcvrStatus.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgRcvrStatus
cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgRcvrStatus.description: This object indicates VPC peer keep-alive message receiving status.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgLastReceiveTime.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgLastReceiveTime
cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgLastReceiveTime.description: This object indicates date and time of VPC peer keep-alive message last received. This object contains value 0x0000010100000000, if peer-keepalive message has never been received.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgReceiveInterface.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgReceiveInterface
cVpcPeerKeepAliveMsgReceiveInterface.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of interface of VPC peer keep-alive message last received.

cVpcRoleTable.name: cVpcRoleTable
cVpcRoleTable.description: The table contains the VPC role status information in the managed device.

cVpcRoleEntry.name: cVpcRoleEntry
cVpcRoleEntry.description: An entry containing VPC role information.

cVpcRoleDomainID.name: cVpcRoleDomainID
cVpcRoleDomainID.description: An arbitrary value to uniquely identify the VPC management domain on the local system. Value zero indicates there is no VPC management domain being configured for this device.

cVpcRoleStatus.name: cVpcRoleStatus
cVpcRoleStatus.description: This object indicates the VPC role status of the peer device. primarySecondary(1) : primary, and operational secondary. primary(2) : primary, and operational primary. secondaryPrimary(3) : secondary, and operational primary. secondary(4) : secondary, and operational secondary. noneEstabished(5) : none peer device.

cVpcDualActiveDetectionStatus.name: cVpcDualActiveDetectionStatus
cVpcDualActiveDetectionStatus.description: This object indicates the dual active detection status of peer device. true(1) : indicate that Dual Active is detected. false(2) : indicate that Dual Active is not detected.

cVpcSystemAdminMacAddress.name: cVpcSystemAdminMacAddress
cVpcSystemAdminMacAddress.description: This object specifies VPC system MAC address.

cVpcSystemOperMacAddress.name: cVpcSystemOperMacAddress
cVpcSystemOperMacAddress.description: This object indicates VPC system operational MAC address.

cVpcLocalOperMacAddress.name: cVpcLocalOperMacAddress
cVpcLocalOperMacAddress.description: This object indicates VPC local system operational MAC address.

cVpcSystemAdminPriority.name: cVpcSystemAdminPriority
cVpcSystemAdminPriority.description: This object specifies VPC system priority.

cVpcSystemOperPriority.name: cVpcSystemOperPriority
cVpcSystemOperPriority.description: This object indicates VPC system operational priority.

cVpcLocalRoleAdminPriority.name: cVpcLocalRoleAdminPriority
cVpcLocalRoleAdminPriority.description: This object specifies VPC local role priority.

cVpcLocalRoleOperPriority.name: cVpcLocalRoleOperPriority
cVpcLocalRoleOperPriority.description: This object indicates VPC local role operational priority.

cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveTable.name: cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveTable
cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveTable.description: The table contains the statistics of VPC peer-keepalive messages in the managed device.

cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveEntry.name: cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveEntry
cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveEntry.description: An entry containing statistics of the VPC peer-keepalive messages.

cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveDomainID.name: cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveDomainID
cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveDomainID.description: An arbitrary value to uniquely identify the VPC management domain on the local system. Value zero indicates there is no VPC management domain being configured for this device.

cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveMsgsSent.name: cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveMsgsSent
cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveMsgsSent.description: This object indicates the number of peer-keepalive messages sent to peer.

cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveMsgsRcved.name: cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveMsgsRcved
cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveMsgsRcved.description: This object indicates the number of peer-keepalive messages received from peer.

cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveAvgInterval.name: cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveAvgInterval
cVpcStatsPeerKeepAliveAvgInterval.description: This object indicates the average interval for the peer-keepalive messages received from peer.

cVpcStatsPeerStatusChangeCount.name: cVpcStatsPeerStatusChangeCount
cVpcStatsPeerStatusChangeCount.description: This object indicates the number of times that the peer status gets changed.

cVpcStatusPeerLinkTable.name: cVpcStatusPeerLinkTable
cVpcStatusPeerLinkTable.description: The table contains the list of VPC peer-links in the managed device.

cVpcStatusPeerLinkEntry.name: cVpcStatusPeerLinkEntry
cVpcStatusPeerLinkEntry.description: An entry containing VPC peer-link management information applicable to a particular VPC domain.

cVpcStatusPeerLinkDomainID.name: cVpcStatusPeerLinkDomainID
cVpcStatusPeerLinkDomainID.description: An arbitrary value to uniquely identify the VPC management domain.

cVpcStatusPeerLinkIfIndex.name: cVpcStatusPeerLinkIfIndex
cVpcStatusPeerLinkIfIndex.description: The value of the ifIndex corresponding to the peer link of this VPC domain.

cVpcStatusHostLinkTable.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkTable
cVpcStatusHostLinkTable.description: The table contains the VPC host-link summary information in the managed device.

cVpcStatusHostLinkEntry.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkEntry
cVpcStatusHostLinkEntry.description: An entry containing VPC host-link summary information.

cVpcStatusHostLinkDomainID.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkDomainID
cVpcStatusHostLinkDomainID.description: An arbitrary value to uniquely identify the VPC management domain.

cVpcStatusHostLinkVpcID.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkVpcID
cVpcStatusHostLinkVpcID.description: An arbitrary value to uniquely identify a VPC link between the host and the switch for a given VPC management domain.

cVpcStatusHostLinkIfIndex.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkIfIndex
cVpcStatusHostLinkIfIndex.description: The value of the ifIndex corresponding to a host-link interface.

cVpcStatusHostLinkStatus.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkStatus
cVpcStatusHostLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the current status of VPC host-link. down(1) : Host link is down. downStar(2) : Local host link is down, forwarding via vPC peer-link. up(3) : Host link is up.

cVpcStatusHostLinkConsistencyStatus.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkConsistencyStatus
cVpcStatusHostLinkConsistencyStatus.description: This object indicates the status of configuration consistency check of this VPC host link.

cVpcStatusHostLinkConsistencyDetail.name: cVpcStatusHostLinkConsistencyDetail
cVpcStatusHostLinkConsistencyDetail.description: This object indicates the reason of consistency check status change detail.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigInfoGroup.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigInfoGroup
cVpcPeerKeepAliveConfigInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects providing peer-keepalive link and messages configuration information.

cVpcPeerKeepAliveStatusInfoGroup.name: cVpcPeerKeepAliveStatusInfoGroup
cVpcPeerKeepAliveStatusInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects providing peer-keepalive status information.

cVpcMIBRoleGroup.name: cVpcMIBRoleGroup
cVpcMIBRoleGroup.description: A collection of objects providing peer-keepalive role information.

cVpcMIBStatisticsGroup.name: cVpcMIBStatisticsGroup
cVpcMIBStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing peer-keepalive statistics information.

cVpcMIBPeerLinkStatusGroup.name: cVpcMIBPeerLinkStatusGroup
cVpcMIBPeerLinkStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects providing peer-link status information

cVpcMIBHostLinkStatusGroup.name: cVpcMIBHostLinkStatusGroup
cVpcMIBHostLinkStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects providing host-link VPC status information.
